# .cursorrules — Workspace Rules & Workflows

## Node.js Environment
- You MUST always use `pnpm` for all node package and script executions.
- Use `pnpm run build` or `pnpm run typecheck` to verify changes before completing your turn.

## Graphify Knowledge Graph Rules
This workspace utilizes **Graphify** to convert codebase architecture and documentation into an ingestion-ready knowledge graph.

- **Check Graph First**: Never perform recursive, high-token directory scans or excessive `grep` queries. Instead, parse the structured knowledge graph stored in `graphify-out/graph.json` or consult `graphify-out/GRAPH_REPORT.md` to understand relationships and boundaries.
- **Workflow**:
  - Run `graphify .` to re-initialize the knowledge graph.
  - Run `graphify . --update` to incrementally sync modifications to components or layouts.
  - Use `graphify . --watch` for real-time synchronization.
- **Output Reference**: Refer to the interactive dependency graph in `graphify-out/graph.html` to visualize component couplings.
